sentences: Léon Bernier (6 September 1936, Hull, Quebec (now Gatineau, Quebec) - 11 October 2011, Longueuil) was a Canadian composer, conductor, pianist, arranger, accompanist, and music pedagogue.
Léon Bernier (6 September 1936, Hull, Quebec (now Gatineau, Quebec) - 11 October 2011, Longueuil) was a Canadian composer, conductor, pianist, arranger, accompanist, and music pedagogue.
In 1962 Bernier founded Les Diplomates du Québec, an award-winning drum and bugle corps which remains active to this day.
He served as pop singer Ginette Reno's music director from 1964 to 1972.
His arrangements for Reno's self-titled album was awarded the Grand Prix du Disque in 1968.
From 1970 to 1972 he was director of a summer concert series at the Place des Arts in Montreal.
Bernier was a pupil of pianist Hélène Landry at the Conservatoire de musique du Québec à Québec where he graduated with a premier prix in piano performance in 1954.
In 1955 he was awarded the Prix d'Europe which enabled him to study under Renzo Silvestri from 1956-1958 at the Accademia Nazionale di Santa Cecilia in Rome.
